[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{It's like a Bridge fantasy come true. But don't go crazy, wait to see what kind of hand partner has. Remember, anything you say will be forcing. So you answer 2NT and he bids 3NT. What is your next bid? 

Hmmm, 22-24 points added to your 16 comes to 38-40 points. Looking apologetically at your poor opponents you bid 7NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:AK.AKT86.75.AKQ6 QJT7.93.KQ2.T984 86.Q752.A9864.53 95432.J4.JT3.J72"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 3H pass 4C pass 4D pass 6H all pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "5c42dde8f3a20fc9ed93d36bb6756a6259f3a07a0dc7d04618478ec1a081dd44"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{Your 7 points isn't enough for a Positive response so you respond 2\D. Partner now bids 2\H. What is your bid? 

You let partner know of your good support by bidding 3\H, which is a stronger bid than 4\H would be. Partner now bids 4\C.  

Partner is not introducing a new suit here, you have already agreed on \Hs. He is making a control-showing bid of the \CA. He expects you to do the same if you can. Since you can show your Ace very conveniently below game level you bid 4\D. That was what he was hoping for, he bids 6\H.}

