[Deal "N:AJ.AKT86.Q94.AKQ T43.J4.J7632.764 KQ9865.7.85.9532 72.Q9532.AKT.JT8"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 2S pass 2NT pass 3S pass 4S all pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "0158a684ee2abdbc66eef24efd75aa6b1ce3db32e1852cebc506924a722c1bad"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{Your 7 points isn't enough for a Positive response so you respond 2\D. Partner now bids 2\H. What is your bid? 

You don't like the \Hs, but with a good suit of your own you can say 2\S. Partner now bids 2NT.  

You know there are enough points for game so you must keep bidding. You should bid the \Ss one more time to show partner it is a 6-card suit. He then bids 4\S and everybody passes.}

